messages.text: Babe, where are you?
Right behind you. I can see you.
I'm getting on the train.
I can't get through the crowd …
I'm on the train already. Hurry! The door is closing!
Shit.
Hurry!
Fuck. Missed it.
Dammit, you're always lagging behind.
Relax, the next F train is 2 mins away.
We're already late. My parents will kill us. You always do this to me.
On the F now. Getting off on 42nd, right?
I'll find you outside. You two go ahead.
What do you mean you TWO?!
JOHNNY ISN'T WITH YOU?
I THOUGHT HE WAS WITH YOU!!
OMG!! JOHHNY!!
Texting him now.
Dammit, we are the worst parents.
You are!
Calm down. I'll get off on the next stop and run back to get him.
He text you back yet?
No.
Shit. What was that noise? We're slowing down.
We are too !!!
What's going on?!
Our train completely stopped.
Mom? Dad?
Johnny, where are you?!
Stay where you are, daddy is coming to get you.
Where are you, dad? All the lights went out.
All the lights?! Are you still where we had the hot dogs??
I think so. Everyone is running around.
Where are you exactly, Johnny?
I don't know.
Everyone is screaming. Mom, I'm scared.
Johnny. Don't move. Daddy's coming.
Do you see a police officer anywhere around you?
I can't see anything. It's so dark.
Shit, how do I get out of this stupid train?
Figure something out!!! Quick!
Johnny? Are you still there?
Yes.
Tell mommy what's happening.
Is there any kind of light that you see?
Someone is waving a flashlight, I think.
Walk over there. It's probably a police officer.
Do what your mom said, Johnny. Go to the man with the flashlight. And wait there.
OK.
That's my boy.
You are very brave, Johnny!
Rachel, text with Johnny, while I try to get out off this train.
OK.
Any progress?
Still stuck on this damn train. Just pulled the emergency switch.
And?
Nothing. The doors are still stuck. How the fuck is everyone so calm?!
Maybe they didn't forget their 9-year old in Times Square during an apocalypse.
Or maybe New Yorkers are just used to this kind of shit.
I never thought I'd say this, but …
I would give anything to be stuck in L.A traffic right now.
Babe, keep texting with Johnny. Avoid words such as apocalypse. Happy stuff, babe. He's scared as it is.
Don't get smart with me now. This is all your fault.
Ugh. Fuck. That hurt!
What did?
Tried to break the window with my fist.
And?
Pretty sure I broke my wrist.
Jesus, Brock!
And the window?
Intact.
Wait, I found something.
What is it?
I'm borrowing this old man's walking cane.
What are you going to do with it???
Pry the door open!!!
Is it working?
Made it! I'm out!
Johnny says the man with the flashlight is not a cop.
He says he's wearing an alien suit and a mask.
A hazmat suit?
I don't know. Just hurry!
Where are you now?
Made it out the train. On the roof of the train car. NOW people are going crazy.
Crazy?!
One of them just grabbed me by the feet and tried to pull me back in.
Hurry. The man in the “alien suit” is taking Johnny somewhere.
Where?!
Why is Johnny not on group text anymore??
Johnny, where are you now, buddy?
I'm with the the scary man with a mask.
His friends all have scary masks too.
Come quick, dad! I'm scared.
I'm on my way, buddy.
You're a real hero, honey.
You are, Johnny! And your dad is on the roof of the train now.
Just like in the movies.
Almost out of the tunnel now.
I can hear the guy playing the banjo at the station. Remember him, Johnny?
Mhm.
See, Johnny, everything's fine. The banjo man is still playing his song.
I can hear the banjo man too!
You can??!!
That means we're very close, buddy! Just stay where you are.
Hurry, dad. The scary men want to put me in their van.
What's going on, Brock?! Who are these people??
Can you see Johnny????
No. Almost there!!
Shit!! The train just started moving again!
Can't you get off???
I'm trying to!!
Not exactly a lot of maneuvering space in these tunnels, you know!!
Be careful!
Our train started moving too.
That's a good sign! They must have figured out what the issue was.
Finally!! I'm off the train. Walking out to the street.
Johnny! Can you still hear the banjo?
No.
The men want to take my phone away.
Hurry, Brockkkk!!!!
I'm in the street. The banjo man is with me, Johnny. Tell me if you can hear it. OK, Johnny?
Johnny??!!
Johnny?!
Did they really take his phone?
Brock???!!! What the hell is going on?
I see him, babe! He heard the banjo!
He's running away from the van.
The billboards are starting to light up again.
There he is!!
I got him, babe. I got our son back. He's fine.
Getting off on 42nd?
Rachel?!!
Raaachel?!!!!
I'm on 42nd.
Thank god. Walking up 42nd now.
Sorry for making us late, babe.
It's not your fault. At least not this time.
From now on we always hold hands.
I see your parents. Are you with them?
Yeah. I see you. And JOHNNY!! Thank god, he's OK!
